cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on the effectiveness of convolutional neural nets (convnets) for tasks requiring correspondence in image understanding. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, since convnets are a type of machine learning model, it is also likely that this paper could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the receptive field sizes of convnet features, which could potentially fall under neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of convnet features in keypoint prediction, which is a task related to multimedia (cs.MM).
